/div><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;=
font-size: 16px;">Writers all know a secret that I want to share with you, =
because whether you consider yourself a writer or not, you&#8217;re writing=
 a story, too:</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-=
height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><strong>Questions reshape your reality.</str=
ong></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26=
px;font-size: 16px;">We all think what we want is answers. We don&#8217;t, =
actually. Answers are dead things. Questions are animating. What we want is=
 great questions.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);li=
ne-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">By the time a question gets its answer, a=
ll of the juice has been squeezed. The answer is the pulp and pith. Answers=
 are static things. Questions are kinetic. I like watching the NBA Draft mo=
re than I like watching any single NBA game. The Draft creates questions. G=
ames are answers.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);li=
ne-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>Actually, fuck answers, the more I =
think about it. The best questions don&#8217;t have answers. The point of t=
he question isn&#8217;t to find </span><em>an </em><span>answer. The best q=
uestions are organizing principles, magnets, ways of seeing.</span></p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size=
: 16px;">Writers know this. Staring at a blank page with no question to ans=
wer is felt proof of Sartre&#8217;s observation: &#8220;Humans are condemne=
d to be free.&#8221; (Maybe it had to be a writer who made that observation=
=2E) Fire up a blank page with a questi=
on in mind, however, and the world bec=
omes grownup Blue&#8217;s Clues. You&#8217;re reading something or talking =
to someone and it&#8217;s almost as if you see a blue paw print and hear li=
ttle kids shouting &#8220;A clue! A clue!&#8221; whenever something you mig=
ht be able to use appears.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,=
55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">What&#8217;s true in writing, I&=
#8217;m arguing, is true (maybe increasingly so) with life.</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"=
>The most important question you can ask yourself, if you don&#8217;t know =
your question already, is &#8220;What question am I trying to answer?&#8221=
; Like with your life. This one actually should have, if not an answer, at =
least a working hypothesis. But since the answer is a question, we&#8217;ll=
 let it slide.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-=
height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>Writers get to do this over and over a=
gain, each time we work on a new piece, </span><em>in silico</em><span>. If=
 I am writing an essay on </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/d=
7e813df-8338-4300-9378-1956a24f86fe?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNua=
MZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: rgb(54,55,55);text-de=
coration: underline;">networking</a><span>, my brain tingles every time I c=
ome across some bit of information that might be useful to explaining netwo=
rking. It is unbelievable to experience the first few times; tidbits I woul=
d have skimmed right over suppressing a yawn in normal times become engross=
ing when they help answer my question.</span></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20=
px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>For a w=
riter, though, each essay is a specific question in service, hopefully, of =
a larger question, and it&#8217;s that larger question that is relevant to =
even those of you who don&#8217;t consider yourself writers, because it&#82=
17;s about how you write the story of your life. This is the question that =
shapes you </span><em>in vivo</em><span>. The one that animates you.</span>=
</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;f=
ont-size: 16px;">This kind of question is like a mission, but with infinite=
 paths &#8211; equally driving but endlessly explorable. A mission is almos=
t too much like an answer, after which you autopilot in pursuit. A question=
 branches. A mission is a wonderful thing, but more people have questions (=
and more of them).</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);l=
ine-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>Over the past few months, I&#8217;=
ve been obsessed with becoming a better writer. That is not my main questio=
n - </span><em>How can I become a better writer? </em><span>- but exists in=
 service of it. Sub-questions are important, too, like side quests, and are=
 made pointier by the existence of your Big Question. So I&#8217;ve tried t=
o read a lot of great essays and profiles &#8211; David Foster Wallace&#821=
7;s </span><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/4b70f309-3bb2-4929-=
a3f8-e0cb966ba200?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6=
m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: rgb(54,55,55);text-decoration: underlin=
e;">David Lynch Keeps His Head</a></em><span> and </span><em><a href=3D"htt=
ps://substack.com/redirect/1715b0c4-f073-47ce-84a1-63f167cafb36?j=3DeyJ1Ijo=
iOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"=
color: rgb(54,55,55);text-decoration: underline;">Roger Federer as a Religi=
ous Experience</a><span>, </span></em><span>and Guy Talese&#8217;s </span><=
em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/f023f2af-4466-44ee-9b01-a63d5ff=
ce80d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" r=
el=3D"" style=3D"color: rgb(54,55,55);text-decoration: underline;">Frank Si=
natra Has a Cold</a><span>, </span></em><span>and Tad Friend&#8217;s </span=
><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/8ca0a06b-0d5c-4b82-8e29-8e91a=
6bad2ae?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU"=
 rel=3D"" style=3D"color: rgb(54,55,55);text-decoration: underline;">The Mi=
nd of Marc Andreessen</a><span> </span></em><span>and </span><em><a href=3D=
"https://substack.com/redirect/0cedc472-3aaf-49dc-a569-719ab1189ecd?j=3DeyJ=
1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=
